Ansible Config File Update
===========================

ansible.cfg

# Uncomment following line to enable SSH on the required user.

#remote_user: <username>

# Save the file

#You can also test this by following steps:
1. Setup passwordless connectivity between ansible controller and target nodes by copying public key of ansible controller node to target users' authorised_keys.
2. Setup the ansible inventory with the hostnames or IPs of the target machine.
3. run below command to verify the user which is being used for SSH towards target machines and run tasks.

# ansible -m ping all -vvvv

# The output will show the user.
